    • Method Detail

      • minus

        public Point3f minus(Point3f p)
        Subtract the values from the given Point with this Point.
        For example:
        Point3f p1 = new Point3f(3, 6, 1);
        Point3f p2 = new Point3f(1, 6, 4);
        Point3f p3 = p1.minus(p2);
        p3 contains the values (2, 0, -3). The values in the other Points remain unchanged.
        Parameters:
        p - The Point to use to subtract from.
        Returns:
        A new Point3f with the values of p - this.

      • minus

        public Point3f minus(float x,
            float y,
            float z)
        Subtract the values from the given values with this Point.
        For example:
        Point3f p1 = new Point3f(3, 6, 1);
        Point3f p2 = p1.minus(1, 6, 4);
        p2 contains the values (2, 0, -3). The values in p1 remain unchanged.
        Parameters:
        x - The horizontal value to subtract from.
        y - The vertical value to subtract from.
        z - The oblique (depth) value to subtract from.
        Returns:
        A new Point3f with the values of values - this.values.

      • plus

        public Point3f plus(Point3f p)
        Add the values from the given Point to this Point.
        For example:
        Point3f p1 = new Point3f(3, 6, 1);
        Point3f p2 = new Point3f(1, 6, 4);
        Point3f p3 = p1.plus(p2);
        p3 contains the values (4, 12, 5). The values in the other Points remain unchanged.
        Parameters:
        p - The Point to use to add to.
        Returns:
        A new Point3f with the values of p + this.

      • plus

        public Point3f plus(float x,
           float y,
           float z)
        Add the values from the given values to this Point.
        For example:
        Point3f p1 = new Point3f(3, 6, 1);
        Point3f p2 = p1.plus(1, 6, 4);
        p2 contains the values (4, 12, 5). The values in p1 remain unchanged.
        Parameters:
        x - The horizontal value to add to.
        y - The vertical value to add to.
        z - The oblique (depth) value to add to.
        Returns:
        A new Point3f with the values of values + this.values.

      • move

        public void move(float dx,
        float dy,
        float dz)
        Move the Point3f instance as if it is a Point in space.
        For example:
        Point3f p = new Point3f(5, 7, -3);
        p.move(-4, 3, 12);
        p now contains the values (1, 10, 9).
        Parameters:
        dx - The amount to move the Point horizontally.
        dy - The amount to move the Point vertically.
        dz - The amount to move the Point obliquely (depth).
